manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Sport Laundry Liquid For dirty or smelly laundry, it's Biokleen to the rescue. Our formulas use powerful plant-derived and mineral-based cleaning agents to breakup stains and eliminate odors, leaving clothes clean, fresh and smelling great. Biokleen Sport is perfect for active families, as it's made with special enzymes to specifically targets odors caused by perspiration. Biokleen Laundry products are highly concentrated to reduce packaging, waste and energy use. Biokleen is proudly manufactured in the U.S. and made with a commitment to people, pets and our planet. Give stains and odors the red card with this bottle of Biokleen Sport. If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to reach out. Ingredients Contains: water, C12-16 pareth-7 (plant-derived), sodium lauryl sulfate (plant-derived), saccharomyces ferment mixture (natural deodorizer), cocamidopropyl betaine (plant-derived), lauramine oxide (plant-derived), sodium chloride (mineral-based), sodium carboxymethyl inulin (plant-derived), glycerin (plant-derived) phenoxyethanol, sodium citrate (plant-derived), lavandula hybrida oil (plant-derived), caprylic/capric triglyceride (plant-derived), eucalyptus globulus leaf extract (plant-derived), rosmarinus officinalis flower extract (plant-derived), lavandula officinalis flower oil (plant-derived), and linalool (plant-derived). Truly 3X Concentrated = 128 HE Loads/64 Standard Loads Special Enzymes Neutralize Odors Caused by Perspiration Extracts of Lavender & Eucalyptus No artificial fragrance or colors Made in the USA

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My go to clean ingredient detergent
reviews.reviewText: Biokleen detergent has truly exceeded my expectations in terms of cleaning power and eco-friendliness. The plant-based formula is a major plus, providing a deep clean without relying on harsh chemicals. It's a relief to know that my clothes are getting clean without compromising the environment.I appreciate the concentrated nature of this detergent – a little goes a long way, making it both cost-effective and reducing packaging waste. The subtle, natural fragrance leaves my laundry with a fresh scent without being overpowering.Stain removal is impressive, even with tough, set-in stains. My clothes come out looking and smelling clean. The fact that it's suitable for high-efficiency machines is a practical feature.Overall, Biokleen detergent aligns with my values of sustainability and cleanliness. If you're looking for an effective, eco-friendly laundry solution, this detergent is an excellent choice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So happy to have found this!
reviews.reviewText: I've used natural detergents for many years, always looking for ones with a natural mild scent that cleans clothes well but that are affordable. This detergent is very concentrated and lasts for so long! We have a family of five with dogs and do lots of laundry. I can't believe my luck to have found a natural detergent so reasonable priced and that lasts so long. It cleans great, has a nice mild citrus scent, and seems to be gentle enough on clothes. I'll be using this for as long as they make it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Wowwwww. This laundry detergent is seriously excellent!! I’m washing clothes daily from an incontinent loved one, and this detergent can handle the entire kit and kaboodle. I previously used 2-4 different cleaning agents to reach a modicum of acceptable cleanliness, but the recommended amount of Biokleen has replaced all of those! (I have an HE machine, and the recommended amount is a slight 1/2 cap - maybe 2 Tablespoons??? ) Clothes are clean and fresh with no lingering odors.The price/load is extremely reasonable!I seriously could make a commercial for Biokleen Laundry Detergent. 👏🏼👏🏼

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for regular laundry; but doesn't do well on tough stains, smells, and funk
reviews.reviewText: I have mixed feelings about this detergent. It's skin and environment friendly, it has a mild pleasant scent, it's cost-effective, and it's readily available in stores in a pinch. However, in terms of it's actual cleaning ability, which is arguably one, if not the most, important consideration, it's hit or miss. On your everyday dirty laundry (aka daily clothing, shower and hand towels, bedding), it does it's job. Everything comes out clean, smelling fresh, and lacks that white residue that can sometimes happen with "green" detergents. Now, on your especially dirty, funky, or stained laundry (e.g. gym clothes, food/blood/grease/oil stains, "my toddler likes to take a bath in the dirt" clothing, fabric dye stains, and anything involving mildew), it fails miserably. Despite trying various methods and settings with this detergent, the stains and smells are still there! I try to pre-treat the stains best I can, but that's hard to do in our busy household with a toddler. I have ended up having to use a different, more-pricey product to deal with this part of the laundry, which as you can imagine, is both frustrating and time consuming. At the end of the day, I'm torn. On one hand, it meets all my requirements for a detergent; on the other hand, it only meets 2/3rds of my "cleaning" needs. Before I give up on this brand, I’ve decided to try the Sports version as I’m hoping that will pack the extra punch and leave all my laundry smelling and looking great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for sensitive skin at a great value
reviews.reviewText: I've been using this detergent for my family since 2020. If you use a HE washer you only need a half capful, and the cap is very small so the large bottle lasts quite a long time. The ingredients work very well for my daughter and I who have sensitive skin. I have also recommended it to our church because they just bought a washer/dryer to clean items for babies in the nursery. A good way to remove the toxic chemicals included in other detergents from your house!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best low sudsing detergent
reviews.reviewText: This is the ONLY detergent that is truly low-sudsing with my water softening system. The scent is very light, hardly noticeable. Wonderful product, I highly recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great, no smell
reviews.reviewText: All you folks with bad reviews, consider checking into your washer! Modern washers don't put nearly enough water into your load, and actually sometimes don't even wet all the clothes! Get a old washer, with no electronics and no frills, those are work horses, and they actually wash your clothes. New washers (last 10-15 years) are JUNK! Get a washer made in the 90s - early 2000s if you actually want your clothes clean
